From: 4noha
Subject: net80211: guard ieee80211_media_status() against NULL ic_bss on resume
License: ISC (this patch modifies OpenBSD source and inherits ISC; see ../LICENSE-ISC)

net80211: guard ieee80211_media_status() against NULL ic_bss on resume.

Problem (2026-06-03..05, DM250 / rk3128, jcs fork):
  Across suspend -> resume with WiFi up, the bwfm detach -> re-attach
  window can leave the net80211 bss node (ic->ic_bss) NULL for a brief
  moment. If netwatchd / ifconfig issues a SIOCGIFMEDIA in that window
  the ifmedia_ioctl() -> ieee80211_media_status() chain dereferences
  ic_bss without guarding and the kernel takes a fatal data abort
  (Translation fault L1).

  Confirmed on the device by ddb + addr2line:
    pc       = ieee80211_media_status
    return   = ifmedia_ioctl

  This is the "next layer" after the earlier resume-crash fixes
  (dwmmc-resume-pwrseq + bwfm-sdio-resume-guard +
  ieee80211_node_detach ba_del). Those eliminated the SDIO error 60,
  the sc_task softc NULL deref, and the armed-BA-on-detach leak — but
  the resume-time ioctl -> media_status NULL deref is not covered by
  any of them and fires here.

  In jcs rk3128, ieee80211_media_status() (around line 787-) has two
  unguarded ic_bss derefs:
    1. The S_RUN condition `ic->ic_bss->ni_port_valid` — if S_RUN +
       M_STA + RSNON with ic_bss == NULL, crash.
    2. case IEEE80211_M_STA: `ni = ic->ic_bss;` immediately followed
       by ni->ni_txmcs / ni->ni_flags / ni->ni_rates.rs_rates[...]
       derefs with no ni == NULL check. This is the line that crashed.

Fix (defensive, minimal):
  1. Guard the S_RUN condition: `ic->ic_bss != NULL &&
     ic->ic_bss->ni_port_valid`. In the NULL window IFM_ACTIVE is not
     set (link reported inactive) which is fine for the brief resume
     transient.
  2. After `ni = ic->ic_bss;` insert `if (ni == NULL) break;` so the
     subsequent ni-> derefs are never reached. With ic_bss == NULL the
     function returns IFM_AVALID-only media (no ACTIVE / rate subtype;
     IFM_AUTO and the trailing ic_curmode 11A/B/G/N/AC/AX flags still
     apply).

  The other cases (IBSS / AHDEMO / HOSTAP / MONITOR) and the
  ic_curmode switch do not touch ic_bss / ni, so no extra guarding is
  needed.

Target: sys/net80211/ieee80211.c::ieee80211_media_status()

CAUTION: this patch only stops the resume from CRASHING in
ieee80211_media_status(). It is NOT a root-cause fix for the
"WiFi survives lid close" goal; the suspend tear-down (see
bwfm-suspend-down.diff v3) plus the dwmmc full power cycle (see
dwmmc-resume-full-cycle.diff) carry that responsibility. This patch is
documentary for the v3 stack — keep applied as a belt-and-braces
guard.

--- sys/net80211/ieee80211.c.orig
+++ sys/net80211/ieee80211.c
@@ -794,12 +794,14 @@ ieee80211_media_status(struct ifnet *ifp, struct ifmediareq *imr)
 	if (ic->ic_state == IEEE80211_S_RUN &&
 	    (ic->ic_opmode != IEEE80211_M_STA ||
 	     !(ic->ic_flags & IEEE80211_F_RSNON) ||
-	     ic->ic_bss->ni_port_valid))
+	     (ic->ic_bss != NULL && ic->ic_bss->ni_port_valid)))
 		imr->ifm_status |= IFM_ACTIVE;
 	imr->ifm_active |= IFM_AUTO;
 	switch (ic->ic_opmode) {
 	case IEEE80211_M_STA:
 		ni = ic->ic_bss;
+		if (ni == NULL)	/* resume/detach race: no bss yet */
+			break;
 		if (ic->ic_curmode == IEEE80211_MODE_11N ||
 		    ic->ic_curmode == IEEE80211_MODE_11AC ||
 		    ic->ic_curmode == IEEE80211_MODE_11AX)
